11/02/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A two-day regional forum on the facts about war crimes in the former Yugoslavia opens Monday (February 11th) in Belgrade.
This third such conference will bring together more than 250 representatives of governments, parliaments, media, war veterans associations and NGOs from the countries of the former Yugoslavia.
Serbian Parliament Speaker Oliver Dulic will open the event, while European Parliament Rapporteur for Serbia Jelko Kacin will deliver a speech.
Discussions will focus on three topics:
the needs and expectations of war crimes victims and their families, the regional approach to war crimes investigations, and efforts to prevent new wars and war crimes.
(Tanjug, RTRS - 10/02/08)
